      <description>&lt;p&gt;One of the unsung heroes of my personal Linux server setups is a simple Node.js application I wrote called &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mattbun/smtp-pushover&#34;&gt;smtp-pushover&lt;/a&gt;. It&amp;rsquo;s a simple &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simple_Mail_Transfer_Protocol&#34;&gt;SMTP&lt;/a&gt; (email sending) server that forwards any email it receives to &lt;a href=&#34;https://pushover.net/&#34;&gt;Pushover&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I recently rewrote it in Go and published the new version as &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mattbun/smtn&#34;&gt;smtn&lt;/a&gt;. It supports other notification services now!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
